<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall ensure that ships flying its flag shall be constructed and maintained in accordance with the hull, machinery and electrical and control installation requirements of a recognized organization. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik tagab, et tema lipu all s&otilde;itvad laevad ehitatakse ja neid hooldatakse koosk&otilde;las tunnustatud organisatsiooni n&otilde;uetega kere, masinate ja elektri- ja juhtimisseadmete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may decide to use rules it considers equivalent to those of a recognized organization only on the proviso that it immediately notified them to the Commission in conformity with the procedure of Directive 83/189/EEC and to the other Member States and they are not objected to by another Member State or the Commission and found through the procedure of Article 13 not to be equivalent. </inglise>
